I dropped soda entirely but it’s mostly time-based. During the week I stick mostly to protein. From 5 pm fri to 5 pm sun i can have what I want provided I really truly want it. So if I’m jonesing hard for pizza I have pizza, I just keep it to a couple of slices. But I found I don’t really give a shit about buns on a burger so even if I have a burger I still skip the bun on weekends, if I have eggs I skip the toast because I realized I really didn’t care about toast, etc. I made tacos for dinner last sat but left off the tortilla for mine because it’s just calories I didn’t care about

So I always have a light at the end of the tunnel. I wanted homemade chocolate chip cookies bad a few weeks back but I’m able to push through and resist during the week because I wa able to have some on Sunday. Having a release valve like that lets me resist the other days vs just giving in on Wed then probably also having them on Sun.
Don’t know if that would work for others but it’s worked for me.
Plus seeing food I just ate out of habit like toast w breakfast vs actually wanting has been interesting
That’s awesome, dude. That’s a lot of time and commitment.
